trend_summary: Across the image sequence the core town spreads slightly outward and hamlets infill, yet fields and woodland remain dominant. Agricultural plots merge into larger blocks and riparian vegetation thickens. Built-up area rises slowly but the landscape still reads as sparsely developed and rural.
notable_changes: Gradual radial expansion of the main central town, mainly to the south and east.
Emergence of ribbon housing along primary roads, increasing linear settlement.
Conversion of isolated farmsteads into small residential clusters.
Field consolidation: hedgerow removal creates larger, uniform agricultural parcels.
Broadening and darkening of riverside vegetation, hinting at riparian restoration.
